Write the constructor method in the Edge class.
Remember to respond with a snippet in the form of the following:
```
class Edge {
    constructor(startVertex, endVertex, NurbsCurve) {
        // your code here
    }
}
```

```javascript
class Edge {
    constructor(startVertex, endVertex, NurbsCurve) {
        if (!startVertex || !endVertex) {
            throw new Error("Edge must have a start and end vertex");
        }
        this.startVertex = startVertex;
        this.endVertex = endVertex;
        this.curve = NurbsCurve;
    }
}
```
